aesi
Class Program

java.lang.Object
  aesi.Program

public class Program
extends java.lang.Object

The main class of this program. Not only does this hold all the variables that define the settings such as what the opponent is or where the log file can be found but also other interesting variables that can be interesting for every class such as the random generator or the reference to the fitness function.

Constant Field Values

DEFAULT_CLASS_FILE_PATH

public static final java.lang.String DEFAULT_CLASS_FILE_PATH
The path that defines how we can reach .class files that can be used by the robocodeEngine. Previously assumed to define the .class alternative to the DEFAUL_JAVA_FILE_PATH. This is used for example by the robocodeEngine which can use it to load the robot the class file defines. All one would need to add is the name and not the .class extension.

See Also:

Constant Field Values

use_fit_gui

public static boolean use_fit_gui

population_size

public static int population_size
The number of chromosomes in a population. More is better but also a lot more time consuming.

nr_of_fitness_rounds

public static int nr_of_fitness_rounds
The number of battles the fitness functions simulates to find the fitness value. When more rounds are simulated the score is more accurate, resulting in a better (more accurate) fitness value. However this is also more time consuming. We should try to strike to golden mean for maximum results.

nr_of_reevaluate_rounds

public static int nr_of_reevaluate_rounds
Once in ten rounds we test if the robot's fitness value is accurate. This is done in this number of rounds.

top_value

public static int top_value
The maximum a value can be in an expression. The ExpressionTree class consists of operators and values, the values can consist of calls but also of numbers. The maximum such a value can be is defined here. Negative values not yet implemented.

chromosome_depth

public static int chromosome_depth
The maximum number of methods in an event. This is probably not needed anymore as the program balances this out itself!!

plays_among_self

public static boolean plays_among_self
When the robot population should evolve against his best candidate, this boolean should be set to true. This means the string opponont will be rewritten to an "BestOf_".

plays_among_self_threshold

public static int plays_among_self_threshold
When the robot population should evolve against his best candidate, this integer indicates after how many rounds they must begin battling themselves. It must not be zero, because in the beginning robots do not know how to fight.

random

public static java.util.Random random
The random generator that is used throughout the program.

opponent

public static java.lang.String opponent
The opponent our populations battles with. This can be any opponent, for example we might want to change this to a bot from the population itself!

print

public static void print(java.lang.Object o)
Prints an object to both the terminal and the log file. Please use this as textual output at any time as previous projects have proven the effectiveness of doing this.

HOWEVER, recently it seemed as if Java had this INBUILT! Further investigation is needed to check if this is the case. We might still be better of using this as it could be extremely handy to have one central place every where output passes through, ready to be managed.

Parameters:
o - The object to print. This could be anything.
